1) git init
2) create out and src folder
3) enter to the Prisma.io
4) go to the typescript part of the prisma.io
5) npm init -y
6) npm install prisma typescript ts-node @types/node --save-dev
7) open tsconfig.json file under the src and out folders
8) write the following statements into tsconfig.json file
            {
                "compilerOptions": {
                "sourceMap": true,
                "outDir": "dist",
                "rootDir" "src",
                "strict": true,
                "lib": ["esnext"],
                "esModuleInterop": true
                }
            }
9) npx prisma init
10) open the .env file
11) open the .gitignore file 
12) write the .env and node_modules into the .gitignore
13) create model in prisma
14) change database URl in .env file
15) create database '....'
16) npx prisma  migrate dev --name 'your migrate name'